article.headline: San Diego St. 79, TCU 77
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas -- Kyle Spain scored 18 points and made all six of his free throws in overtime of San Diego State's 79-77 victory against TCU on Saturday night. Spain finished 10-of-10 on free throws and grabbed a loose ball in the final seconds of overtime when teammate Lorrenzo Wade blocked a 3-point attempt to preserve a one-point lead. Spain was fouled and made his final two free throws for a 79-76 lead with 7 seconds left. Richie Williams had 14 points and 11 rebounds for the Aztecs (19-8, 9-5 Mountain West), who scored all 10 of their overtime points on free throws. Wade had 12 points, seven rebounds, five assists and three blocks. Ronnie Moss led TCU with 22 points, and Keith Langford had 18, including two free throws with 24 seconds left to send the game to overtime tied at 69. Zvonco Buljan had 11 points and 11 rebounds.
